                  </hi>. I am foreman to George Bird, a builder, in Edge<lb></lb>ware-road—the prisoner was employed on the sewers there. On 22nd of September I discharged him, and gave him a note for 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—on the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184210240191"></xptr>
               <p>Saturday morning following he came to the works, and asked me to ac<lb></lb>commodate him, because it was nearly two miles to go to my employers—I said I would pay him the money, and asked for the note that I gave him—he said he had lost it—I paid him 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he went away with it—this is the note I gave him.</p>
               <p>
