                  </hi>. I am clerk to George Bird. On the morning of the 24th of September the prisoner came and produced this note—I paid him three half-crowns, and four shillings, which was the amount of his wages—if he had not brought me that note I should not have paid him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> In January last Handley borrowed 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. of me; he never paid me; I was afraid to ask him, for fear be should discharge me. On the 23rd he discharged me; I asked him for the 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; he did not pay me, but gave me a note for 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. I went again, and he wrote me an order for 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
